[3]
Date: Tue, 28 Apr 1998 12:28:24 +0000
From: Gil Katzenstein <gkatzens@msms.doe.k12.ms.us>

All cases I have seen in the literature about iatrogenic CJD and human
derived hormones indicate that the hormone(s) was PITUITARY-derived (no
living donors, only cadavers). My understanding is that hCG is of placental
origin, therefore, the only potential risk would be associated with
placentally purified hCG.
Both experimentally and epidemiologically, some tissue is considered to be
non-infectious (incapable of causing disease, neuropathology changes in the
recipient +/or generation of PrPres, the abnormal, disease-associated
isoform). Urine, I suspect, is in this category.
--
Gil E. Katzenstein, Ph.D.
Science Faculty,
Mississippi School for Mathematics and Science
e-mail: gkatzens@msms.doe.k12.ms.us
